{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1c4b0d79-1fbd-422c-aef8-4d6f3e002c27","content":"Here are the common options depending on your stack:\n\n**ASP.NET Core (`dotnet new`)**\n- `webapi` — minimal API or controller-based\n- Auth options: `--auth Individual` (Identity/JWT), `--auth IndividualB2C` (Azure AD B2C), `--auth SingleOrg` (Azure AD), `--auth Windows`\n\n**Node.js / Express**\n- Use `express-generator` or scaffold manually\n- Auth: Passport.js (JWT, OAuth2, local), Auth0 SDK, Firebase Auth\n\n**Python / FastAPI**\n- Scaffold with `fastapi` + `uvicorn`\n- Auth: OAuth2 with JWT (built-in support), `python-jose`, `passlib`\n\n**Example (ASP.NET Core with JWT):**\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi -n MyApi --auth Individual\n```\n\n**Example (Node.js with Passport JWT):**\n```bash\nnpx express-generator MyApi\ncd MyApi && npm install passport passport-jwt jsonwebtoken\n```\n\nWould you like me to scaffold a project with a specific stack and auth type?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"272516b7-f991-4d50-a1d7-de0bd1e76b9c","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking a general knowledge question about web API project templates and authentication options. This doesn't require any tool calls - I can answer from my knowledge of common web frameworks.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer covering the most popular options.","outputTokens":326},"id":"71c184e9-a4ed-42c4-8e9c-ffc2dbfd8124","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:50:15.975Z","parentId":"17be6f58-9cb5-4544-8c96-90f0cde92707"}
